<DOC><DOCNO> AP880324-0122 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-24-88 1215EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-BRF--DisneyDress-Code     03-24 0171</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Disney Dress-Code,0175</SECOND><HEAD>Disneyland Hotel Suspends Six For Failure To Shave</HEAD><DATELINE>ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Six Disneyland Hotel workers who rebelledagainst the Magic Kingdom's ban on facial hair were suspended forthree days without pay and given an order to shave or be fired.   The hotel's 1,600 workers recently came under the famedamusement park's dress and grooming codes when their former boss,the Wrather Corp., sold the property to the Walt Disney Co.   The dress code, established in 1957, bans facial hair on men,mandates short haircuts and bars women from wearing heavy makeup,long fingernails or excessive jewelry.   The six suspended Wednesday have until Monday to shave or losetheir jobs, said Disneyland spokesman Bob Roth.   A dozen male employees have been issued warnings for facialhair, and although half of those shaved, all 12 filed grievanceswith their unions.   Earlier Wednesday, the five unions representing hotel workersunited in opposition to the Disney dress code, but wouldn't saywhether they were willing to strike over it.</TEXT></DOC>